---
title: Orange Chicken & Bell Pepper Stir-Fry with Dark Meat Chicken, Rice & Cashews
description: Got a craving for restaurant-worthy orange chicken? Our fresh spin hits the table in just 20 minutes, thanks to our tangy orange sauce! You'll sizzle juicy dark meat chicken with green peppers in a hot skillet, toss in that magic savory-sweet sauce, and serve it all over fluffy rice. Add a sprinkle of cashews for crunch, and dig right in!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/678ed0508cb13d9592827749-589c3b44.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/678ed0508cb13d9592827749-en-US.pdf
servings: 2
cuisine: East Asia
author: Sara Heilman
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 740 kcal
  fat: 21 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 100 g
  sugar: 25 g
  protein: 33 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 580 mg
time required: 20 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/orange-chicken-and-bell-pepper-stir-fry-678ed0508cb13d9592827749
---

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @Onion{1}(peeled and diced into 1/2-inch pieces). Core, deseed, and dice @Green Bell Pepper{1}(deseeded and diced into 1/2-inch pieces). Roughly chop @Cashews{1/2%ounce}.

Open package of chicken and drain off any excess liquid. In a #medium bowl{}, combine @Diced Skinless Dark Meat Chicken{10%ounce}, @Cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}; toss until thoroughly coated.

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; cook, undisturbed, until browned on one side, ~{3%minutes}. Add @Onion{} and @Green Bell Pepper{}; cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is cooked through and veggies are browned and tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @Orange Sauce{3%ounce}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, and @water{2%TBSP}. Cook, stirring constantly, until chicken and veggies are thoroughly coated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Stir in @Butter{1%TBSP}.

Divide rice and chicken stir-fry between shallow #bowls{} in separate sections. Sprinkle @Cashews{} over rice. Drizzle chicken stir-fry with as much @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.